E4Plus1.uk.description: Kiss Kiss, Bang Bangalore: Mr Burns outsources the plant to India and puts Homer in charge of training the workforce. Patty and Selma kidnap a celebrity. (S17 Ep17/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Good, the Sad and the Drugly: A volunteer inspires Bart to become a better person. Lisa writes an essay about what Springfield will be like in 50 years' time. (S20 Ep17/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Blazed and Confused: Bart tricks his family into going to a strange desert festival known as Blazing Guy so that he can get revenge on his sadistic new teacher, Mr Lassen. (S26 Ep7/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: First Dates
E4Plus1.uk.description: Double-divorcee and 'hopeless romantic' Ian hopes it's third time lucky with Amy. Scientist Gerald meets 'free spirit' Lisa. And will nervous Danny regret his five pre-date pints? (S16 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: Britain's sharpest armchair critics have been watching: Sitting on a Fortune, Close to Me, You, Nadiya's Fast Flavours, Animal, UFO Witness and This Morning. (S18 Ep9)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: What do the Goggleboxers think of The Graham Norton Show; Mary Berry - Love to Cook; Celebrity Antiques Road Trip; Strictly; The Lakes with Simon Reeve; and Sex: Unzipped? (S18 Ep10)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Open House: The Great Sex...
E4Plus1.uk.description: ...Experiment: Jamie and Sharmayne remain unsure about how far they can go. And can seasoned swingers Ashley and Tanya take the next step and have sex with others on their own? (S3 Ep8)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Celebrity First Dates
E4Plus1.uk.description: Jess from Made in Chelsea, weather presenter Sian Lloyd, Daniel Brocklebank (vicar Billy from Corrie) and Musharaf from Educating Yorkshire go on dates with members of the public. (Ep4/4) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Gogglebox
E4Plus1.uk.description: Britain's sharpest armchair critics have been watching: Sitting on a Fortune, Close to Me, You, Nadiya's Fast Flavours, Animal, UFO Witness and This Morning. (S18 Ep9) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Below Deck Sailing Yacht
E4Plus1.uk.description: My Super Sideways Sixteen: Daisy confronts chef Cloyce about his underwhelming meals. Will he sink or swim with a sweet 16 celebration? (S5 Ep7/16)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Graduates: Manny's father, Javier, shows up for his graduation and takes him out on a wild night of celebration. Then Jay steps in to pick up the pieces. (S8 Ep22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Last of the Red Hat Mamas: Marge joins a women's group after Homer humiliates her at a party and her old friends shun her. But are her new friends all they seem to be? (S17 Ep7/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Comic-Con Conundrum: Cut off from his father's fortune, Raj appoints Sheldon to organise his finances. Penny considers joining the guys at Comic-Con. (S10 Ep17)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Escape Hatch Identification: Leonard and Penny offer Sheldon's old room to Raj when he's forced to move out of his flat, leading to unexpected conflict. (S10 Ep18)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Neighborhood
E4Plus1.uk.description: Welcome to the Barbershop: When Dave drops by Calvin's long-time barbershop, he's quickly embraced by its owner and patrons, much to Calvin's consternation. (S1 Ep7)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Neighborhood
E4Plus1.uk.description: Welcome to Thanksgiving: Dave and Gemma host a memorable Thanksgiving in their new home when Dave's politically incorrect mother, Paula, visits from out of town. (S1 Ep8)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Neighborhood
E4Plus1.uk.description: Welcome to the Dinner Guest: When Calvin and Tina learn Marty has a new girlfriend, they insist he invite her over for dinner, with surprising results. (S1 Ep9)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Heavy Is the Head: Will Phil have to rethink his property dream? And Cam has to go to hospital but refuses to have an MRI scan because of a traumatic childhood incident in a well. (S8 Ep14)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Finding Fizbo: Cam is enraged when he sees a clip of someone desecrating his beloved Fizbo costume, so he sets out on a quest to restore Fizbo's good name. (S8 Ep15)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Rude(ish) Tube Shorts
E4Plus1.uk.description: A short, cheeky clip featuring animals and food, from the always hilarious Tube that is Rude.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Luigi's: Gordon Ramsay travels to Orange County, Southern California, to try to save Italian restaurant Luigi's from disaster. (S5 Ep5) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Park's Edge: In Atlanta, Gordon helps first-time restaurant owners Richard and Jorge, whose establishment is in trouble due to their constant fighting, poor food and bad vibes. (S5 Ep6) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Mansion Family: Mr Burns leaves town for a full medical check-up, leaving the Simpsons in charge of his mansion. Guest starring Britney Spears as herself. (S11 Ep12/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Saddlesore Galactica: Homer and Bart save a horse from the fair and decide to train him as an American footballer. Or maybe a racehorse. (S11 Ep13/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Locomotive Manipulation: Love is in the air when Amy convinces Sheldon to join her for a romantic train trip to Napa Valley to celebrate Valentine's Day. (S7 Ep15)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Table Polarization: Leonard buys a dining table for the flat but Sheldon objects to such a big change inside his home. Meanwhile, Howard gets the chance to return to space. (S7 Ep16)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Egg Drop: Jay and Claire take control of their kids' school projects from Manny and Luke, while Haley and Gloria help Phil with a real estate presentation. (S3 Ep12)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Little Bo Bleep: The family help Claire prepare for her upcoming televised debate with Duane Bailey for the town council seat, but will they do more harm than good? (S3 Ep13)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Line Substitution Solution: Sheldon pays Stuart to spend the afternoon shopping with Amy so that he can queue up to see a special film screening instead. (S9 Ep23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Convergence Convergence: Conflict arises when Leonard's recently divorced parents and Sheldon's devoutly religious mother are all in town at the same time. (S9 Ep24)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Conjugal Conjecture: The gang face an awkward morning after Sheldon's mother and Leonard's father share an evening together. Penny's family arrive in town. (S10 Ep1)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Military Miniaturization: Howard has a meeting with Air Force representative Colonel Williams about the gyroscope he invented with Leonard and Sheldon. (S10 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Honeypot: Peralta and Captain Holt clash over the merits of Holt's newly hired assistant. The team attempt to clean and declutter the communal office. (S6 Ep7)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
E4Plus1.uk.description: He Said, She Said: Captain Holt suspects a cunning escape after discovering that his lifelong criminal arch-nemesis has died in a prison transport accident. (S6 Ep8)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Behind the Laughter: A behind-the-scenes look at the Simpson family. How did they win their fame? And how did they cope when the showbiz pressure got too much? (S11 Ep22/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Springfield Splendor: Lisa and Marge team up on a graphic novel that becomes a musical. But Marge takes all the credit... (S29 Ep2/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Separation Agitation: Howard and Bernadette are upset when they leave Halley at the nursery. Bert the geologist introduces his girlfriend to the gang. (S10 Ep21/24)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Cognition Regeneration: Leonard isn't happy when he finds out that Penny is considering accepting a job offer from her ex-boyfriend Zack. (S10 Ep22/24)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Collaboration Fluctuation: Leonard, Penny and Raj settle into their new living arrangement, and Sheldon expresses an interest in Amy's professional life. (S10 Ep19)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Big Bang Theory
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Recollection Dissipation: Sheldon collaborates on two projects - one with Leonard and Howard, plus another with Amy - pushing himself to the limit. (S10 Ep20)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Wettest Stories Ever Told: When the Simpsons' plans for a meal at The Frying Dutchman are ruined, they try to salvage the night by telling three tales of disaster at sea. (S17 Ep18/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Girls Just Want to Have Sums: When Principal Skinner gets cancelled for sexism, the school gets a new principal who mollycoddles the girls. So Lisa disguises herself as a boy. (S17 Ep19/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Father Knows Worst: Marge finds a sauna in the basement but doesn't tell anyone about it. Homer decides to get more involved in the children's education. (S20 Ep18/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Covercraft: Homer forms a band with four other dads, but their modest early success is soon overwhelmed by the breakout potential of lead singer Apu. (S26 Ep8/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: First Dates
E4Plus1.uk.description: Luxury car seller Sam likes his women 'fast and topless'. Is ex-teacher MJ open to Sam's kinky sex desires? Black belt Keira meets former footballer Max. (S16 Ep3)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Monster Hunter
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2020) Paul WS Anderson's sci-fi action starring Milla Jovovich, based on the game of the same name. A US Army Ranger must fight her way out of a parallel world full of monsters.

Film4.uk.title: A Man Called Otto
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Darkly-tinged but ultimately feel-good comedy starring Tom Hanks as a grumpy misanthrope who spends his time badgering people into following society's rules. But why is he like this?

Film4.uk.title: Nuns on the Run
Film4.uk.description: (1990) Eric Idle and Robbie Coltrane star as small-time crooks who accidentally steal £1m and are forced to hide in a convent to escape both the police and the mob.

Film4.uk.title: The Eyes of Tammy Faye
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Jessica Chastain puts in a barnstorming performance as the glitzy televangelist in the kind of real-life rise and fall that just seems made for the movies. With Andrew Garfield.

Film4.uk.title: Time Lock
Film4.uk.description: (1957) Gripping drama with Robert Beatty. An expert team races against the clock to save a six-year-old boy who's been trapped in a seemingly impregnable bank vault.

Film4.uk.title: They Rode West
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Tough western. A cavalry doctor (Robert Francis) discovers a Native American tribe is dying of malaria, but his by-the-book captain (Phil Carey) refuses to allow their treatment.

Film4.uk.title: Fire Down Below
Film4.uk.description: (1957) Drama with Rita Hayworth, Robert Mitchum and Jack Lemmon. Two friends agree to smuggle a mysterious European woman across the border, but she soon has them at each other's throats.

Film4.uk.title: Roman Holiday
Film4.uk.description: (1953) Audrey Hepburn won her only Oscar in this romance as a bored princess who runs away from her duties and meets an American journalist (Gregory Peck), who shows her Rome.

Film4.uk.title: Sleepless in Seattle
Film4.uk.description: (1993) Romantic comedy with Tom Hanks and Meg Ryan. A bereaved man gets another chance at love when his son puts him on a radio talk show.

Film4.uk.title: The Green Mile
Film4.uk.description: (1999) Drama with Tom Hanks and Michael Clarke Duncan. Strange events occur when a man convicted of raping and murdering two young girls arrives on death row in a Louisiana prison.

Film4.uk.title: The Last King of Scotland
Film4.uk.description: (2006) Oscar and BAFTA-winning Forest Whitaker stars as Idi Amin - the murderous Ugandan dictator, who mesmerises a young Scottish doctor, played by James McAvoy.

Film4.uk.description: Teleshopping.

Film4.uk.title: Saraband for Dead Lovers
Film4.uk.description: (1948) Historical drama starring Joan Greenwood and Stewart Granger. Princess Dorothea marries the future king of England. But then she meets a Swedish count...

Film4.uk.title: Storm over the Nile
Film4.uk.description: (1955) Drama. Anthony Steel stars as a disgraced soldier who, during the British army's 1898 campaign in Sudan, goes way beyond the call of duty to prove his courage. With Laurence Harvey.

Film4.uk.title: The Wackiest Ship in the Army
Film4.uk.description: (1961) World War II comedy starring Jack Lemmon. A luckless naval lieutenant is duped into commanding a dangerous mission into enemy territory during the Battle of the Bismarck Sea.

Film4.uk.title: Hangman's Knot
Film4.uk.description: (1952) Civil War-era Western. A unit of Confederate soldiers attack a Union troop to steal gold. Learning that the war is over, they must finish the mission in disguise.

Film4.uk.title: Gemini Man
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Will Smith stars in Ang Lee's action-thriller as both an over-the-hill hitman and the young clone of himself sent to take him out. With Clive Owen.

Film4.uk.title: Bridge of Spies
Film4.uk.description: (2015) Tom Hanks and Mark Rylance star in Steven Spielberg's Cold War spy drama. After gaining notoriety for defending a Soviet spy, a US lawyer then tries to free a CIA pilot.

Film4.uk.title: Mean Streets
Film4.uk.description: (1973) Scorsese's classic crime drama about the ordinary lives of mafiosi - the boredom, casual violence and shattered dreams - in Little Italy, with Harvey Keitel and Robert De Niro.

Film4.uk.title: The Double
Film4.uk.description: (2013) Dark psychological thriller. Jesse Eisenberg stars as a timid man whose drab existence takes a turn for the worse with the arrival of a new colleague at work. With Chris Morris.

Film4.uk.title: Kind Hearts and Coronets
Film4.uk.description: (1949) This dark comedy from Ealing studios sees Alec Guinness take on the roles of eight characters, all the noble victims of a vengeance-seeking relative, played by Dennis Price.

Film4.uk.title: San Demetrio, London
Film4.uk.description: (1943) Fact-based drama about a group of Merchant Navy sailors who brave fire and the ocean to save the San Demetrio oil tanker after it's almost destroyed by a German cruiser.

Film4.uk.title: Man in the Saddle
Film4.uk.description: (1951) Western. Randolph Scott stars as a rancher who's the target of unwelcome harassment by his richer and more powerful neighbour. With Alexander Knox, Joan Leslie and Ellen Drew.

Film4.uk.title: The Iron Petticoat
Film4.uk.description: (1956) Comedy with Katharine Hepburn and Bob Hope. A Russian captain defects to London, falls for the charms of Major Lockwood, and tries to convince him of the beauty of communism.

Film4.uk.title: Turner & Hooch
Film4.uk.description: (1989) Comedy-thriller starring Tom Hanks. A cop investigates a murder to which there's just one witness: Hooch, a slobbering, beer-drinking French mastiff, who now needs 24/7 protection.

Film4.uk.title: Anna
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Luc Besson's action thriller about a young Russian assassin, with Sasha Luss. A scout offers Anna an opportunity to become a model in Paris, but can she escape her links to the KGB?

Film4.uk.title: The Black Phone
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Horror with Ethan Hawke. Denver 1974 and The Grabber is snatching boys from the street. But he doesn't reckon on two kids with uncanny abilities who refuse to do as they're told.
